<!-- ============================================================================
     InDows module: timezone
     Sets the time zone automatically. Without it, Windows uses the region picked
     during the first-run setup.

     WHERE: settings pass="specialize" > component "Microsoft-Windows-Shell-Setup"
     ANCHOR (a comment in the base) named:   [InDows:module] specialize-shell-setup

     REPLACE: __TIMEZONE__  with a Windows time-zone ID (NOT a city/offset).
       List them with:   tzutil /l        (or  Get-TimeZone -ListAvailable )
       Examples: "Romance Standard Time" (FR/CET), "GMT Standard Time" (UK),
                 "Pacific Standard Time", "Eastern Standard Time", "UTC"
     ============================================================================ -->
<TimeZone>__TIMEZONE__</TimeZone>
